<div id="tab_plugin_octogoat" class="tab-pane">
<div class="container-fluid octogoat-ui">

<div class="octogoat-hero">
<div class="octogoat-title-wrap">

<div class="octogoat-title-logo">
<img class="octogoat-goat-overlay"
src="/plugin/octogoat/static/img/octogoat_icon.svg"
alt="OctoGOAT">
<h2 class="octogoat-title">OctoGOAT</h2>
</div>

<div class="octogoat-tagline">
Save time. Save money. Save that print.
</div>

</div>
</div>

<div class="octogoat-nav-row">

<div class="octogoat-nav-left">

<button class="btn octogoat-nav-btn"
data-toggle="modal"
data-target="#pricing-modal"
title="placeholder">
Pricing </button>

<button class="btn octogoat-nav-btn"
data-toggle="modal"
data-target="#howto-modal"
title="placeholder">
How To </button>

<button class="btn octogoat-nav-btn"
data-toggle="modal"
data-target="#contact-modal"
title="placeholder">
Contact </button>

</div>

<div class="octogoat-nav-right">

<span class="label label-success"
data-bind="visible: licenseValid()">
License Valid </span>

<span class="label label-important"
data-bind="visible: !licenseValid()">
License Required </span>

</div>

</div>

<div class="octogoat-card">

<h4>Inputs</h4>

<div class="row-fluid">

<div class="span4">
<label>Measured Print Height (mm)</label>

<input type="number"
step="0.1"
class="input-block-level octogoat-input"
placeholder="22.0"
data-bind="value: measuredHeight"
title="placeholder">

</div>

<div class="span4">
<label>Quadrant</label>

<select class="input-block-level octogoat-input"
title="placeholder">

<option>Left-Front</option>
<option>Left-Back</option>
<option>Right-Front</option>
<option>Right-Back</option>

</select>
</div>

<div class="span4">
<label>Layer Height (mm)</label>

<input type="number"
step="0.01"
class="input-block-level octogoat-input"
placeholder="0.2"
data-bind="value: layerHeight"
title="placeholder">

</div>

</div>

<button class="btn btn-large btn-block octogoat-action-btn"
data-bind="click: buildResume, enable: licenseValid()"
title="placeholder">

RECONSTRUCT GCODE AND PROCEED TO CALIBRATE POSITION

</button>

</div>

<div class="octogoat-card"
data-bind="visible: resumeBuilt()">

<h4>CALIBRATE MY POSITION</h4>

<div class="octogoat-warning-box">

*Warning! While possible to resume a failed print in seconds by simply clicking
"Set Assumed Position" and skipping to Resume Now, it is not recommended!

Is it awesome? Yes, but a safe and precise resume only takes a couple more minutes.

If something doesn't look right you can always cut power and try again.

If the print is still on the bed, with OctoGoat it's not dead.

Be safe! Be kind! And know you are appreciated.

OctoGoat powered by Lazarus. Patent pending. All rights reserved.

</div>

<div class="row-fluid">

<div class="span4">

<button class="btn btn-block octogoat-function-btn"
data-bind="click: applyPark"
title="placeholder">

1 — ASSUMED POSITION

</button>

</div>

<div class="span4">

<button class="btn btn-block octogoat-function-btn"
data-bind="click: goToDatum"
title="placeholder">

2 — MOVING ON TO PERFECTION

</button>

</div>

<div class="span4">

<button class="btn btn-block octogoat-function-btn"
data-bind="click: lockDatum"
title="placeholder">

3 — POSITION CALIBRATION COMPLETE

</button>

</div>

</div>

</div>

<div class="octogoat-card">

<h4>Resume GCode Preview</h4>

<pre class="octogoat-preview"
data-bind="visible: resumeBuilt(), text: previewText"></pre>

</div>

<div class="octogoat-card octogoat-resume-card">

<label class="checkbox octogoat-checkbox">

<input type="checkbox"
data-bind="checked: motionAcknowledged">

I acknowledge toolhead has been aligned, nozzle temp is correct and it is safe to move

</label>

<button class="btn btn-large octogoat-resume-btn"
data-bind="enable: motionAcknowledged() && resumeBuilt(), click: resumeNow"
title="placeholder">

RESUME PRINT

</button>

</div>

</div>
</div>
